<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="ru">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Результат — Задание 4</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f7f7f7;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 30px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #0077cc;
      font-size: 36px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .status {
      font-size: 24px;
      color: green;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
    .reading-box {
      background-color: #ffffff;
      padding: 40px;
      margin: 0 auto 40px;
      max-width: 1600px;
      width: 95%;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      border-radius: 12px;
      font-size: 30px;
      text-align: left;
      line-height: 1.9;
    }
    .nav-button, .play-btn, .download-btn {
      background-color: #0077cc;
      color: white;
      padding: 16px 32px;
      margin: 12px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-size: 20px;
      cursor: pointer;
      text-decoration: none;
      display: inline-block;
    }
    .nav-button:hover, .play-btn:hover, .download-btn:hover {
      background-color: #005fa3;
    }
    audio {
      margin: 20px 0;
      width: 80%;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Результат сохранён</h1>
  <div class="status">✅ Вы успешно завершили задание. Вы можете прослушать или скачать запись ниже.</div>

  <audio id="audio" controls></audio>
  <br>
  <button class="play-btn" onclick="playAudio()">▶️ Прослушать</button>
  <button class="download-btn" onclick="downloadAudio()">⬇️ Скачать запись</button>

  <div class="reading-box">
    <b>4 Task. Imagine that you and your friend are doing a school project “Spending holidays: in the city or in the countryside”.</b><br><br>
    You have found some photos to illustrate it but for technical reasons you cannot send them now. Leave a voice message to your friend explaining your choice of the photos and sharing some ideas about the project. In 2.5 minutes be ready to:
    <ul>
      <li>explain the choice of the illustrations for the project by briefly describing them and noting the differences;</li>
      <li>mention the advantages (1–2) of the two ways of spending holidays;</li>
      <li>mention the disadvantages (1–2) of the two ways;</li>
      <li>express your opinion on the subject of the project – which way of spending holidays presented in the pictures you would prefer and why.</li>
    </ul>
    <b>You will speak for not more than 3 minutes (12–15 sentences). You have to talk continuously.</b>
  </div>

  <a href="../ege4.html" class="nav-button">Перейти к выбору варианта</a>
  <a href="../../../ege.html" class="nav-button">Перейти к выбору задания</a>
  <a href="../../../ege_menu.html" class="nav-button">Перейти к выбору режима</a>
  <a href="/oge-trainer/index.html" class="nav-button">Перейти на главную</a>

  <script>
    const audio = document.getElementById("audio");
    const base64 = sessionStorage.getItem("ege4_audio_base64");
    if (base64) {
      audio.src = base64;
    } else {
      document.body.innerHTML += "<p style='color:red'>❌ Запись не найдена.</p>";
    }

    function playAudio() {
      if (audio.src) {
        audio.play();
      } else {
        alert("Запись не найдена.");
      }
    }

    function downloadAudio() {
      if (!base64) {
        alert("Запись не найдена.");
        return;
      }
      const a = document.createElement("a");
      a.href = base64;
      a.download = "ege4_recording.webm";
      a.click();
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
